# Frontend QA Audit Report — Richwell Portal

**Stack**: React 19 + Vite 7 + Axios + React Hook Form + React Router v7 + Lucide Icons
**Date**: 2026-03-11 | **Files Scanned**: 125 source files across `src/`

---

## 1. Critical Issues (P0 — Fix Immediately)

### 🔴 CRIT-01: Duplicate Route for `/student/grades`
**File**: [index.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/routes/index.jsx#L319-L330)

Two different components are mounted on the **same path**:
```diff
- <Route path="/student/grades" element={<GradeHistory />} />   ← Line 320
- <Route path="/student/grades" element={<MyGrades />} />       ← Line 329
```
**Impact**: Only one will ever render (first match wins). `MyGrades` is dead code.
**Fix**: Remove or rename the duplicate route (e.g., `/student/grades/history`).

---

### 🔴 CRIT-02: Duplicate Route for `/admin` Dashboard
**File**: [index.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/routes/index.jsx#L208-L221)

`AdminDashboard` is registered **twice** under different `PageWrapper` titles:
```diff
- Line 208: <Route path="/admin" element={<AdminDashboard />} />  (inside "Academic Management" wrapper)
- Line 220: <Route path="/admin" element={<AdminDashboard />} />  (inside "Admin Dashboard" wrapper)
```
**Impact**: The first match wins, rendering Admin Dashboard with the **wrong page title** ("Academic Management").
**Fix**: Remove the duplicate at line 208.

---

### 🔴 CRIT-03: Duplicate Route for `/admin/audit`
**File**: [index.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/routes/index.jsx#L223-L244)

`AuditLogList` is registered in **both** ADMIN and REGISTRAR route groups:
```
Line 223: Admin group → /admin/audit
Line 244: Registrar group → /admin/audit
```
**Impact**: Route shadowing; confusing permission model.
**Fix**: Keep only one definition, or use a shared route group.

---

### 🔴 CRIT-04: Duplicate Imports in Route Index
**File**: [index.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/routes/index.jsx)

```diff
- Line 61: import ProfessorDashboard from '../pages/faculty/ProfessorDashboard';
- Line 145: import ProfessorDashboard from '../pages/faculty/ProfessorDashboard'; ← DUPLICATE

- Line 59: import StudentDashboard from '../pages/student/StudentDashboard';
- Line 149: import StudentDashboard from '../pages/student/StudentDashboard';    ← DUPLICATE
```
**Impact**: Build warnings; can cause build failures with strict linting or module system issues.

---

### 🔴 CRIT-05: [useFetch](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/hooks/useFetch.js#4-36) Hook Has Stale Closure Bug
**File**: [useFetch.js](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/hooks/useFetch.js#L31)

```js
[url, options] // ← options is an object, compared by reference
```
Since `options` is an object literal, it creates a **new reference on every render**, causing `fetchData` to be recreated infinitely in `useCallback`. Any `useEffect` depending on `fetchData` will trigger an infinite loop.

**Fix**: Serialize `options` via `JSON.stringify` or accept stable primitive params.

---

## 2. Security Issues (P1)

### 🟠 SEC-01: JWT Tokens Stored in `localStorage`
**Files**: [axios.js](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/api/axios.js), [AuthContext.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/contexts/AuthContext.jsx)

Tokens are stored in `localStorage`, which is vulnerable to XSS attacks. Any injected script can read `localStorage.getItem('access_token')`.

> [!CAUTION]
> If any XSS vector exists (3rd-party library, browser extension, etc.), the attacker gets full API access.

**Fix**: Use `httpOnly` cookies for token storage (requires backend changes).

---

### 🟠 SEC-02: No CSRF Protection on API Calls
**File**: [axios.js](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/api/axios.js)

No CSRF token header is sent with state-changing requests. If you ever switch to cookie-based auth, this becomes critical.

---

### 🟡 SEC-03: [ErrorBoundary](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/pages/errors/ErrorBoundary.jsx#5-43) Exposes Stack Trace in Production (Conditional)
**File**: [ErrorBoundary.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/pages/errors/ErrorBoundary.jsx#L31)

Uses `process.env.NODE_ENV` check which is correct, but verify Vite sets this properly. Vite uses `import.meta.env.MODE`, not `process.env.NODE_ENV`.

**Fix**: Replace `process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development'` with `import.meta.env.DEV`.

---

### ✅ SEC-PASS: No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` or `innerHTML` Usage
Zero instances found. This is excellent.

---

## 3. Performance Issues (P1)

### 🟠 PERF-01: Zero Code Splitting — All 30+ Pages Eagerly Imported
**File**: [index.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/routes/index.jsx)

All ~35 page components are imported statically at the top of [routes/index.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/routes/index.jsx). No `React.lazy()` or `Suspense` usage anywhere.

**Impact**: The initial JS bundle loads ALL role-specific pages, even those the user will never visit. A Student downloads all Admin, Registrar, Cashier, Dean, and Professor pages.

**Fix**: Use `React.lazy()` + `<Suspense>` for each page import.

---

### 🟠 PERF-02: No `AbortController` in API Calls — Memory Leak Risk
**Files**: All 35+ pages with `useEffect` + API calls

None of the `useEffect` cleanup functions cancel in-flight requests. If a user navigates away while an API call is pending, the response callback still executes on an unmounted component.

**Fix**: Add `AbortController` to the [useFetch](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/hooks/useFetch.js#4-36) hook or individual page effects.

---

### 🟡 PERF-03: [useIdleTimer](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/hooks/useIdleTimer.js#5-58) Event Listeners Not Throttled
**File**: [useIdleTimer.js](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/hooks/useIdleTimer.js#L40-L42)

Five event listeners (`mousedown`, `mousemove`, `keydown`, `scroll`, `touchstart`) fire [resetTimer()](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/hooks/useIdleTimer.js#15-30) on **every event** — which calls `clearTimeout` + `setTimeout` twice per event. On `mousemove`, this could fire 60+ times/sec.

**Fix**: Add a throttle wrapper (e.g., 1-second debounce on [resetTimer](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/hooks/useIdleTimer.js#15-30)).

---

### 🟡 PERF-04: [logout](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/contexts/AuthContext.jsx#10-11) Function Not Memoized
**File**: [AuthContext.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/contexts/AuthContext.jsx#L140-L146)

[logout](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/contexts/AuthContext.jsx#10-11) is a plain function, not wrapped in `useCallback`. It creates a new reference every render, causing re-renders in all consumers (Sidebar, IdleTimer, ProtectedRoute).

---

