const DeanDashboard = () => <div className="p-8">Dean Dashboard</div>;
```
This renders plain text with no layout, stats, or navigation.

---

### 🟡 UX-03: Limited Responsive Breakpoints
Only **14 `@media` queries** across the entire CSS codebase. Most pages rely solely on Tailwind-style utility classes embedded inline. The following areas have **zero responsive CSS**:

- Admin Dashboard, Audit Log, Faculty Management, Room Management
- All report pages (COR, Masterlist, Graduation)
- Cashier pages, Dean Scheduling page

---

### 🟡 UX-04: Inconsistent Empty/Loading/Error State Patterns
Some pages (e.g., `StudentDashboard`, `RegistrarDashboard`) have proper loading spinners and empty states. Others (e.g., `GradeEntry`, `SchedulingPage`) silently show empty content or have inconsistent error displays.

---

### 🟡 UX-05: Modal Missing Escape Key Handler & Focus Trap
**File**: [Modal.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/components/ui/Modal.jsx)

The modal handles `aria-modal` and `aria-labelledby` (good), but:
- ❌ No Escape key listener to close
- ❌ No focus trap (Tab can escape to background elements)
- ❌ No initial focus management

