## 5. Accessibility Issues (P2)

### 🟡 A11Y-01: Only 8 Files Use `aria-` Attributes
Most page-level components have **zero** ARIA attributes. Specifically:
- Tables have no `role="table"`, `aria-label`, or `scope` attributes
- Form error messages are not linked via `aria-describedby`
- Toast notifications not announced to screen readers (`role="alert"` missing on container)
- Sidebar navigation missing `role="navigation"` and `aria-current="page"`

---

### 🟡 A11Y-02: No Skip-to-Content Link
No skip navigation link exists for keyboard users to bypass the sidebar.

---

## 6. Code Quality Issues (P3)

### 🟡 CQ-01: [ProgramHeadDashboard](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/routes/index.jsx#64-143) Defined Inline in Route File
A full 80-line component with state, hooks, and JSX is defined inside [routes/index.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/routes/index.jsx). This should be in its own file at `pages/program-head/ProgramHeadDashboard.jsx`.

---

### 🟡 CQ-02: Frontend API URLs Don't Match Backend Kebab-Case
**File**: [students.js](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/api/students.js#L9-L15)

```js
returningStudent: (id, data) => api.post(`students/${id}/returning_student/`, data),
manualAdd: (data) => api.post('students/manual_add/', data),
```
Backend was refactored to use `returning-student` and `manual-add` (kebab-case). Frontend API clients still use `snake_case` URLs → **API calls will 404**.

---

### 🟡 CQ-03: Grades API Module is Minimal
**File**: [grades.js](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/api/grades.js)

Only exposes [getHistory()](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/frontend/src/api/grades.js#4-5). All other grade operations (submit midterm, submit final, resolution workflow, credit, uncredit) are called inline in page components instead of through a centralized API module.

---

